131
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:04,401
Are these from our
recon mission?

132
00:09:05,145 --> 00:09:07,136
No, sir. The recon mission
was aborted.

133
00:09:07,213 --> 00:09:08,544
These are from Blackbird.

134
00:09:11,418 --> 00:09:12,646
Thrace.

135
00:09:13,486 --> 00:09:16,683
She took off
and did the whole
recon mission alone.

136
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:20,522
My gods,
look at these shots, Jack.

137
00:09:21,795 --> 00:09:25,253
She put her nose
right up their backsides,
and they never even knew it.

138
00:09:25,332 --> 00:09:27,857
Admiral, I still have
Commander Adama on the line,

139
00:09:27,934 --> 00:09:30,494
and our fighters are still
requesting instructions.

140
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:32,037
Should they resume the attack?

141
00:09:44,718 --> 00:09:46,686
All right. Joint recall.

142
00:09:47,721 --> 00:09:50,417
Both ships stand-down
to Condition Two.

143
00:09:50,757 --> 00:09:53,954
Then I want you to report
to me directly. In person.

144
00:09:54,294 --> 00:09:57,354
I have no intention
of cooling my heels
in your brig.

145
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,126
Fine.

146
00:10:03,336 --> 00:10:05,964
Neutral ground.
Colonial One, no aides.

147
00:10:07,007 --> 00:10:08,440
Be there in 15 minutes.

148
00:10:11,511 --> 00:10:13,103
Stand-down, Condition Two.

149
00:10:25,492 --> 00:10:26,982
There you are.

150
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:30,182
ROSLlN: Let's start this
by admitting an ugly truth.

151
00:11:30,256 --> 00:11:33,748
What happened out there today
was the result of failure
in leadership

152
00:11:33,827 --> 00:11:35,852
of everyone in this room.

153
00:11:35,929 --> 00:11:38,056
We are the leaders
of this fleet.

154
00:11:38,164 --> 00:11:40,325
As such, we need
to set an example.

155
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:43,028
We cannot continue
to let the conflicts
between us...

156
00:11:43,103 --> 00:11:46,004
Oh, let's cut through
the hand-holding, shall we?

157
00:11:46,072 --> 00:11:48,939
Two of his men murdered
one of my officers

158
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:51,033
while protecting a Cylon.

159
00:11:51,111 --> 00:11:53,102
They're guilty.
They admitted it.

160
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:56,606
And under regulations
I have complete authority

161
00:11:56,683 --> 00:11:58,446
to try, convict
and sentence them.

162
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:03,511
And you and I both know
that the penalty
for that crime is death.

163
00:12:04,858 --> 00:12:07,884
Admiral, surely
the spirit of the law

164
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:11,328
requires something more here
than summary executions.

165
00:12:15,568 --> 00:12:19,231
Is this what the two of you
have been doing
for the past six months?

166
00:12:20,039 --> 00:12:23,805
Debating the finer points
of Colonial law?
Well, guess what?

167
00:12:23,877 --> 00:12:25,538
We're at war.

168
00:12:26,446 --> 00:12:30,212
And we don't have the luxury
of academic debate
over these issues.

169
00:12:31,151 --> 00:12:32,641
You want to cut through it,
fine.

170
00:12:35,421 --> 00:12:38,049
You have Pegasus,
he has Galactica.

171
00:12:38,892 --> 00:12:41,861
Two heavily armed,
very powerful warships.

172
00:12:41,961 --> 00:12:45,089
Now, I am sure that Pegasus
would prevail in any fight.

173
00:12:45,165 --> 00:12:47,099
